CAPE TOWN - The African National Congress (ANC) in the Western Cape has on Tuesday called on President Cyril Ramaphosa and Police Minister Bheki Cele to urgently intervene in the dismissal of the provincial head of detectives Jeremy Vearey. On Monday, news broke that he'd been fired after being found guilty of misconduct relating to Facebook posts referencing national commissioner Khehla Sitole. ALSO READ: DA notes dismissal of WC top cop Vearey, calls for stability within SAPS Dismissal of WC detectives chief Vearey raises concerns of stability within SAPS Western Cape ANC spokesperson Dennis Cruywagen said: “We are angered by this dismissal. General Vearey has become an officer hated by criminals in our province. His dismissal appears to be part of a pattern that seems to sideline people’s soldiers. Clearly, there is a crisis in the SAPS." Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android device.